The article is a transcript of speeches given at a Diwali celebration at the White House. The First Lady, Jill Biden, spoke about the significance of celebrating light on the darkest night and the importance of community. Vice President Kamala Harris shared her personal memories of celebrating Diwali and spoke about the holiday's message of hope. President Joe Biden thanked the attendees for their contributions to American culture and emphasized the need to combat hate and bring light to the world. He also mentioned the challenges facing the world today and called for unity and engagement to shape a better future.